repast.simphony.freezedry

Class FreezeDryedObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • repast.simphony.freezedry.FreezeDryedObject

  • public class FreezeDryedObject
extends java.lang.Object
    This represents a flattened object. The properties stored in this object can be one of four types: String, Number, byte[] or FreezeDryedParentChild. As such, when working with this object, one should take care to neither put another object type in as a value, or expect anything else out. These were chosen as the base primitives for this class because for any object it should be possible to decompose the properties into these types. FreezeDryedParentChild represents a flattened view of another object, so that should account for all possibilites.
